        options: ["Start aspirin 81 mg daily — benefit clearly outweighs bleeding risk at this ASCVD level","Shared decision-making is appropriate for ages 40-59 with ≥10% risk, weighing cardiovascular benefit against GI bleeding risk","Aspirin is no longer recommended for any primary prevention indication","Start aspirin only if the patient also has diabetes mellitus"],
