      name: "Ceftazidime-Avibactam (Avycaz)",
      type: "Third-generation cephalosporin + novel beta-lactamase inhibitor",
      action: "Ceftazidime inhibits bacterial cell wall synthesis; avibactam is a non-beta-lactam beta-lactamase inhibitor that protects ceftazidime from degradation by Ambler class A (KPC), class C (AmpC), and some class D (OXA-48) carbapenemases — extending activity to carbapenem-resistant Enterobacteriaceae (CRE)",
      sideEffects: "Diarrhea, nausea, vomiting, headache, elevated transaminases, C. difficile infection, seizures in renal impairment if dose not adjusted",
